Privacy Policy – C0DA-3: Guardian of the Wild

Last updated: May 2026

C0DA-3: Guardian of the Wild is a video game developed for educational purposes.

This application does not collect, store, or share users’ personal data.

The application does not use user accounts, login systems, advertising, in-app purchases, external analytics, or tracking systems.

Locally stored data

The game may save progress information only on the user’s device, such as:

- game progress
- energy cores obtained
- screws collected
- save date
- basic game preferences, such as the selected language

This data is stored locally on the user’s device and is not sent to the developer or to any third parties.

Children

The application may be used by children, but it does not knowingly collect personal information from children or from any other users.

Third parties

The application does not share data with third parties.

Security

Since the application does not collect personal data or send it outside the user’s device, no external processing of personal information is performed.

Changes to this policy

This privacy policy may be updated in the future if new features are added to the application. Any changes will be reflected on this same page.

Contact

For any questions about this privacy policy, you can contact the developer through the email address provided on the Google Play listing.
